recalls.Component: FUEL SYSTEM, GASOLINE:DELIVERY:HOSES, LINES/PIPING, AND FITTINGS
recalls.Summary: Ferrari North America, Inc. (Ferrari) is recalling certain 2022-2023 Ferrari 296 vehicles.  The fuel tank connecting pipe may corrode due to unintended contact between the fuel tank connecting pipe and the high-voltage battery protection cover, potentially resulting in a fuel leak.
recalls.Consequence: A fuel leak in the presence of an ignition source increases the risk of a fire.
recalls.Remedy: Owners are advised not to drive their vehicles until the remedy has been completed.  Dealers will install a new fuel tank connecting pipe reinforced with a protective sleeve, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed July 14, 2023.  Owners may contact Ferrari customer service at 1-201-816.2668.  Ferrari's number for this recall is RC 85.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

issues.title: V6 Engine Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: Excessive oil consumption in the twin-turbo V6 engine, requiring frequent top-offs between service intervals. Some owners report consuming up to 1 quart per 1000 miles.
issues.fix_description: Engine teardown and piston ring replacement, valve seal replacement, or complete engine rebuild in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, use only specified oil grade, avoid aggressive driving during break-in period

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Actuator Failure
issues.description: Premature failure of turbocharger wastegate actuators causing reduced power, engine fault codes, and potential turbocharger damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty wastegate actuators and associated control modules
issues.prevention: Regular turbocharger system inspections, avoid prolonged high-boost operation

issues.title: Dual-Clutch Transmission Jerking
issues.description: 8-speed DCT transmission experiencing harsh shifts, jerking during acceleration, and clutch engagement issues, particularly in stop-and-go traffic.
issues.fix_description: Software calibration updates, clutch pack replacement, or transmission overhaul
issues.prevention: Proper warm-up procedures, avoid riding the clutch in traffic, regular transmission service

issues.title: Battery Management System Faults
issues.description: Hybrid system battery management issues causing loss of electric assist, charging problems, and system warning lights.
issues.fix_description: Battery management system software updates, high-voltage battery cell replacement, or complete battery pack replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid deep discharge cycles, maintain proper charging habits, regular hybrid system diagnostics

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Separation of carbon fiber layers in body panels, particularly around wheel wells and door edges, causing cosmetic and structural concerns.
issues.fix_description: Complete panel replacement with improved manufacturing process panels
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, proper storage conditions, regular inspection

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: Central infotainment display freezing, becoming unresponsive, or displaying error messages, affecting navigation and vehicle settings.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, infotainment module replacement, or complete system reprogramming
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid extreme temperatures, proper shutdown procedures

issues.title: Brake System Overheating
issues.description: Carbon-ceramic brake discs experiencing premature wear and overheating during track use, leading to reduced braking performance and potential safety issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake discs and pads with updated specifications, brake cooling system modifications
issues.prevention: Proper brake cooling periods during track use, high-quality brake fluid, regular brake inspections

issues.title: Active Suspension Control Module Failure
issues.description: Electronic suspension control modules failing, causing suspension to default to comfort mode and loss of adaptive damping functionality.
issues.fix_description: Replace suspension control modules and recalibrate system parameters
issues.prevention: Avoid harsh impacts, regular system diagnostics, proper wheel alignment

issues.title: Fuel System Vapor Lock
issues.description: Fuel system experiencing vapor lock issues in high ambient temperatures, causing starting difficulties and engine stalling.
issues.fix_description: Fuel system ventilation improvements, fuel pump replacement, fuel line insulation upgrades
issues.prevention: Avoid parking in direct sunlight, use high-quality fuel, regular fuel system maintenance

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Electronic door handle mechanisms failing to extend or retract properly, potentially trapping occupants or preventing entry.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle actuator mechanisms and associated wiring
issues.prevention: Regular lubrication of mechanisms, gentle operation, protection from freezing conditions

editorial.tagline: Hybrid evolution of Ferrari's pure racing soul
editorial.hero_blurb: The 296 GTB rewrites the supercar playbook with electrified fury that delivers 818 horsepower from a screaming twin-turbo V6. This isn't just Ferrari's future—it's a masterclass in how hybrid technology can amplify rather than dilute the prancing horse experience.
editorial.essence: Ferrari's first V6 road car since the Dino proves that downsizing doesn't mean compromising on emotion. The 296 GTB combines a high-revving twin-turbo V6 with electric assistance to create a powerplant that's both brutally efficient and intoxicatingly dramatic.
editorial.heritage: Born from Ferrari's Formula 1 hybrid expertise and named after its 2.9-liter displacement and 6-cylinder configuration, the 296 GTB represents the boldest departure from V8 tradition since the brand's founding. It draws inspiration from the legendary Dino models while pushing Ferrari into its electrified future.
editorial.design_philosophy: Pure sculptural elegance meets aerodynamic efficiency in a package that's unmistakably Ferrari yet refreshingly modern. Every curve serves both beauty and function, from the dramatic side air intakes to the active rear spoiler that emerges at speed.
editorial.motorsport_history: The 296 GTB's V6 hybrid architecture directly descends from Ferrari's Formula 1 power units, bringing race-proven technology to the road. Its lightweight construction and advanced aerodynamics echo lessons learned from decades of motorsport dominance.
editorial.engine_character: The twin-turbo V6 screams to 8,500 rpm with an intensity that defies its smaller displacement, while the electric motor fills any torque gaps with instantaneous thrust. It's a masterpiece of engineering that somehow maintains Ferrari's emotional connection despite the technical complexity.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed dual-clutch transmission snaps through gears with violent precision, whether you're crawling through traffic or attacking apex after apex. Paddle shifts deliver race-car immediacy with civilized refinement when needed.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Surgically precise yet surprisingly forgiving, the chassis balances track-focused capability with real-world usability. The advanced suspension manages to be both compliant over broken pavement and razor-sharp when you're chasing lap times.
editorial.steering_feel: Perfectly weighted and rich with feedback, the steering connects you directly to the front wheels with typical Ferrari precision. There's just enough assistance to keep fatigue at bay without isolating you from the road surface.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon-ceramic brakes provide fade-free stopping power with excellent pedal feel and modulation. The system inspires complete confidence whether you're trail-braking into a chicane or panic-stopping from triple digits.
editorial.sound_signature: The V6 produces a unique howl that's distinctly Ferrari yet refreshingly different—part Formula 1 shriek, part exotic turbo whistle. The optional sport exhaust amplifies this symphony while maintaining civility when neighbors are sleeping.
editorial.ideal_owner: Perfect for the Ferrari purist who embraces technological evolution and wants the latest in hybrid performance without sacrificing the emotional connection that defines the marque.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Traditional V8 or V12 devotees who view any form of electrification as heresy, or those seeking maximum exclusivity in an increasingly common supercar segment.
editorial.buyers_summary: The 296 GTB proves Ferrari can evolve without losing its soul, delivering more performance than ever while maintaining the emotional intensity that separates it from clinical competitors. It's expensive and complex, but rewards the committed enthusiast with one of the most complete supercar experiences money can buy.
cons: Complex hybrid system raises long-term reliability questions
